    ns1:bibliographyType "Bibliografía"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000026/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Assessments will be based on your overall number of points earned out of the total possible points.
- Progressive evaluation: 40% of final grade.
- Global evaluation: 60% of final grade.
Further minor adjustments in final grades may be made at the discretion of the instructor based upon attendance and class participation. If you havent?t passed the minimal grade to gain the learning outcomes of the module, a final exam will be provided. The final exam will last 120 minutes. Continuous assessment exercises will be submitted in Moodle unless otherwise is indicated. The instructions for the exam solutions will be given to the students when necessary.
The results will follow the scheme established by the UPM in 2024 as A: Excelent, B: Advanced, C: Satisfactory, D: Not satisfactory.
The primary venue for our classes will be on site at Informatics building in Montegancedo. However, please note that on certain occasions, due to unforeseen circumstances, sessions may transition to an online format. The main content for exam questions will be derived from the material covered during our classroom interactions. At times, questions may also source from textbook readings or other references highlighted during lectures. For theoretical portions of the course, we?ll predominantly employ presentations and whiteboard tools to enhance understanding. On the practical side, labs will be centered around the R programming language. Throughout the duration of the course, class notes and pertinent materials will be shared with all participants via Teams.
This course emphasizes the practical application of plant breeding concepts, primarily through exercises in R. Consequently, the use of computers and proficiency in R programming is essential to grasp these concepts fully. To ensure a seamless learning experience, please install both R and RStudio on your computers prior to our sessions."""@es ;
